{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_87","type":"agent_message","text":"The direct native repro finally exposed the hidden root cause: this isn’t another reflection miss. The BC PKCS#8 decrypt path fails because `org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.BouncyCastleProvider` is being introduced at runtime instead of being registered at native-image build time. I’m searching the repo for how this project models additional security providers in metadata so I can encode it the repo’s way rather than bolting on a one-off workaround."}}
