{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_182","type":"agent_message","text":"The more correct native-image fix appears to be static provider registration, not runtime provider creation. I’m validating that by building the scratch repro with a temporary `java.security.properties` file that pre-registers BC, so the driver’s `Security.addProvider(new BouncyCastleProvider())` becomes a no-op and existing build-time provider instances are used."}}
